mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;possible ways OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>case 4:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math> possible ways OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>case 5:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;possible ways OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>adds their probabilities&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for adding at least <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> of their probabilities (denominator <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>216</mn></math>).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0185</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0370</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0277</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0277</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0185</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0370</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0092</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>38</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>19</mn><mn>108</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>176</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>varies <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> and determines possible values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correctly determines one of the following four cases&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correctly determines another case from the following four cases&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correctly determines the remaining two cases&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>case 1:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> possible ways OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>216</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>case 2:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></mat